     <div style="text-align: center;"><h1 style="color: darkgoldenrod;font-size: 50px;text-align: center;">KYLIAN MBAPPE</h1>
    <img src="https://live-production.wcms.abc-cdn.net.au/ffa2b22aadc52f55fe7d293a9f0c7780?impolicy=wcms_crop_resize&cropH=2667&cropW=4000&xPos=0&yPos=0&width=862&height=575" width="400"></div>
     <h2 style="color:darkgoldenrod;text-align: center;font-size: 30px;">The Brightest Star<br>
    <br>
TRIVIA:</h2>
    <p style="color: darkgoldenrod;text-align: center;font-size: 20px;">Full Name: Kylian Mbappé Lottin <br><br>


Date of Birth: December 20, 1998  <br><br>


Birthplace: Paris, France  <br><br>


Nationality: French<br><br><br></p>
     <div style="text-align: center;color: darkgoldenrod;font-size: 20px;"><h2>MBAPPE'S CAREER</h2><h3>Breakthrough at AS Monaco</h3>
        <img src="https://media.gettyimages.com/id/643497678/photo/manchester-england-kylian-mbappe-of-as-monaco-celebrates-as-he-scores-their-second-goal-during.jpg?s=612x612&w=0&k=20&c=tseSpLQoMvaM1-Si7-dzWrgsUqB5YeuHnNn3vRdDv3Y=" style="float:right; width: 280px; margin-right: 120px;">
        <p style="margin-left: 120px;margin-right: 500px;">
         Kylian Mbappé made his professional debut for AS Monaco at the age of 16, instantly showcasing blistering pace and skill. In the 2016–17 season, he exploded onto the European scene, scoring 26 goals in all competitions. He was instrumental in Monaco’s Ligue 1 triumph, their first in 17 years, and guided them to a UEFA Champions League semi‑final.By the end of the season, he had become one of football’s most sought‑after young talents.
</p><br>
<h3>World Champion at 19</h3>
<img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/56/25/0a/56250ac33e05e6f655a586a486fdc6c4.jpg"width="210" style="float:left; margin-left: 70px;">
<p style="margin-left:400px;margin-right:120px;">
    Mbappé entered the 2018 FIFA World Cup in Russia as France’s youngest player. He became a breakout star, scoring four goals, including two against Argentina in the Round of 16. In the final against Croatia, he netted a crucial strike to secure France’s second World Cup. At 19, he was only the second teenager after Pelé to score in a World Cup final. He won the tournament’s Best Young Player award and became a global superstar overnight.</p>
        
    <br>
    <h3> Dominating Ligue 1 with PSG</h3><img src="https://pbs.twimg.com/media/FPcUMNSXEA86hM4.jpg:large" style= float:right; width="330px;margin-right:30px;">
<p style="margin-right:380px ;margin-left: 350px;">After his breakout at Monaco, Mbappé signed for Paris Saint‑Germain in 2017 in a record transfer deal.
He quickly became the face of French football. At PSG, he won multiple Ligue 1 titles, domestic cups, and individual scoring awards.
He became the club’s all‑time top scorer, surpassing Edinson Cavani with over 250 goals.
His speed, finishing, and dribbling terrorized defenses both in France and Europe.</p><br>

<h3>Hat‑trick Hero in the Final</h3>
<img src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQqhW4u8UqVo0Nuuio26pIUnLsKAC2PZbxRzWFEZ7m6xPzH1f-DdwxOjZ7bW13uTPOE3oE&usqp=CAU" style="width: 250px;float: left;margin-left: 35px;" >
<p style="margin-left: 350px ;margin-right:250px;">Four years later, Mbappé returned to the biggest stage at the Qatar World Cup.
He led France to another final, scoring an incredible eight goals during the tournament.
In the final against Argentina, Mbappé scored a historic hat‑trick — only the second in World Cup final history.
He also won the Golden Boot as the top scorer of the tournament.
Though France narrowly lost, Mbappé’s heroics cemented him as one of football’s biggest icons.</p>
<br><br>
<h3>A New Era at Real Madrid</h3>
<img src="https://assets.goal.com/images/v3/bltf84864c2d1921a81/Kylian%20Mbappe%20Real%20Madrid%20HIC.jpg?auto=webp&format=pjpg&width=3840&quality=60" style="width:380px ;float:right;">
<p style="margin-right: 400px;margin-left: 350px;">After years of speculation, Mbappé finally joined Real Madrid in 2024.
His arrival was seen as the beginning of a new Galáctico era at the Bernabéu.
Mbappé wasted no time, winning the pichichi and european golden boot in his first season , even though the entire team struggled.
At just 25, he is already regarded as one of the greatest players of his generation.</p><br><br>
